Only the hardiest pilgrims come and worship here.
只有最艰难的朝圣者来这里敬拜.

61
00:04:59,060 --> 00:05:00,910
It said that if you drink at Gaumukh,
它说,如果您在Gaumukh喝酒,

62
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,413
you'll live for 100 years.
你会活一百年.

63
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,270
But the true headwaters of the Ganges begin
但是恒河的真正源头开始了

64
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:11,170
above the glacier,
在冰川之上

65
00:05:12,380 --> 00:05:15,130
nearly four and a half thousand meters above sea level.
海拔近四千五百米

66
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:20,303
Few animals can survive in this harsh environment.
在这种恶劣的环境中,很少有动物能够生存.

67
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:30,390
A Himalayan blue sheep's dense fur helps insulate it
喜马拉雅蓝绵羊的茂密皮毛有助于绝缘

68
00:05:30,390 --> 00:05:35,390
against the cold,but even here,predators are on the prowl.
抵御寒冷,但即使在这里,掠食者也在四处寻觅.

69
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:41,363
Snow leopards are perfectly adapted to mountain life.
雪豹非常适合山区生活.

70
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,653
Wooly fur keeps out the cold wind.
毛茸茸的皮毛挡住了冷风.

71
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:55,420
Its long,thick tail can be wrapped around its body,
它的长而粗的尾巴可以包裹在身体上,

72
00:05:55,420 --> 00:05:56,561
like a scarf.
像围巾

73
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:03,290
Even the soles of its feet are covered with fur,
甚至它的脚底都被皮毛覆盖,

74
00:06:03,290 --> 00:06:04,423
for extra warmth.
为您带来额外的温暖.

75
00:06:08,830 --> 00:06:13,090
Minerals in rocks supplement a blue sheep's meager diet,
岩石中的矿物质补充了蓝羊的微薄饮食,

76
00:06:13,090 --> 00:06:14,890
but they need to be eaten with care.
但需要小心食用.

77
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:20,590
Rock falls are common.
岩崩很常见.

78
00:06:30,570 --> 00:06:33,950
Constant freeze and thaw makes mountain slopes unstable
不断的冻结和融化使山坡不稳定

79
00:06:38,980 --> 00:06:42,543
A blue sheep which has lost its footing is an easy meal.
失去立足点的蓝羊是一顿轻松的饭.

80
00:06:51,130 --> 00:06:54,233
Snow melt from the Himalayas continually feeds the Ganges.
来自喜马拉雅山脉的积雪不断地滋养恒河.

81
00:06:56,370 --> 00:06:59,820
Hindu mythology tells that Ganga,the river goddess,
印度神话告诉我们,河女神甘加（Ganga）

82
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:01,853
originally flowed through the heavens.
最初流过天堂.

83
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:06,750
She was brought to earth by a devout king,Bhagiratha,
她由虔诚的国王巴吉拉塔（Bhagiratha）带到世上,

84
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:09,913
whose ancestors had been turned to ashes by an angry sage.
他们的祖先被愤怒的圣人化为灰烬.

85
00:07:12,370 --> 00:07:14,560
The goddess Ganga agreed to come and release
恒河女神同意来释放

86
00:07:14,560 --> 00:07:16,490
these trapped souls.
这些被困的灵魂.

87
00:07:16,490 --> 00:07:18,840
But warned that her torrential power
但是警告说她的洪流力量

88
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,313
would wash the world away.
会洗净世界.

89
00:07:21,630 --> 00:07:23,730
Bhagiratha petitioned Lord Shiva for help.
Bhagiratha向湿婆大人求助.

90
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:26,870
Shiva put his matted hair in the path
湿婆把他乱蓬蓬的头发放在路上

91
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:28,750
of the heavenly river.
天河的.

92
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:32,700
His dreadlocks absorbed the torrent's destructive force
他的辫子吸收了洪流的破坏力

93
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:36,373
and split the deluge into a thousand smaller streams.
并将洪水分成几千条较小的溪流.

94
00:07:39,940 --> 00:07:42,950
The fast flowing mountain brooks are full of insect larvae
快速流动的山间小溪里充满了昆虫幼虫

95
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:47,123
and an ideal hunting ground for a brown dipper.
和一个理想的狩猎场,一个棕色的北斗星.

96
00:07:52,032 --> 00:07:54,000
Weighing less than 100 grams,
重量不到100克,

97
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,560
these small birds seem likely
这些小鸟似乎很可能

98
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,210
to be washed away by the current,
被潮流冲走,

99
00:08:00,650 --> 00:08:02,980
but they're well adapted to forage for food
但它们很适合觅食

100
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,258
in the rocky stream bed.
在多岩石的河床上.

101
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:11,130
The short wings are strong enough to swim under water
短的翅膀足够坚固,可以在水下游泳

102
00:08:11,130 --> 00:08:14,740
and their blood stores more oxygen than terrestrial birds,
而且他们的血液比陆生鸟类存储更多的氧气,

103
00:08:14,740 --> 00:08:18,040
allowing them to hold their breath for half a minute,
让他们屏住呼吸半分钟,

104
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,853
ample time to grab a beak full.
有足够的时间抓住喙.

105
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:27,670
The young Ganges River that flows from the Gangotri Glacier
从甘戈特里冰川流出的年轻恒河

106
00:08:27,670 --> 00:08:30,700
is called Bhagirathi,in honor of the king
被称为Bhagirathi,以纪念国王

107
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:32,700
that brought the river goddess to earth.
把河女神带到了人间.

108
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:36,630
50 kilometers downstream,
下游50公里,

109
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:38,610
the turbulent Bhagirathi collides
湍急的巴吉拉提相撞

110
00:08:38,610 --> 00:08:40,870
with one of its sister streams,
与它的一个姐妹流一起,

111
00:08:40,870 --> 00:08:42,967
the sedate and muddy Alaknanda.
宁静而浑浊的阿拉克南达.

112
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:48,800
The two run alongside each other for 200 meters
两人并排跑了200米

113
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,373
before their waters mix.
在他们的水混合之前.

114
00:08:51,730 --> 00:08:54,393
This river is now called Ganges.
这条河现在称为恒河.

115
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:03,450
Raging water calms as the river reaches the flat lands
随着河流到达平坦的土地,汹涌的河水平静下来

116
00:09:03,450 --> 00:09:04,823
of the Gangetic Plains.
恒河平原.

117
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:09,909
Sediments carried from high among the glaciers are released.
冰川中高处的沉积物被释放.

118
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:17,383
The Ganges deposits 1.6 billion tons of sediment every year,
恒河每年沉积16亿吨沉积物,

119
00:09:18,410 --> 00:09:20,113
four times as much as the Amazon.
是亚马逊的四倍

120
00:09:21,940 --> 00:09:24,813
This creates some of the most fertile land in the world.
这创造了世界上最肥沃的土地.

121
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:35,960
