The Terai is home to one of the largest animals
Terai是最大的动物之一的家

128
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:06,547
in the world,the Indian rhino.
在世界上,印度犀牛.

129
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:12,733
Males can weigh up to 3000 kilos,
雄性重达3000公斤,

130
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:16,463
twice the weight of the average family car.
是普通家庭汽车重量的两倍.

131
00:10:19,980 --> 00:10:23,453
Indian rhinos once roamed right across the Gangetic Plains.
印度犀牛曾经在恒河平原上漫游.

132
00:10:24,340 --> 00:10:27,113
But now are found in just a few protected areas.
但是现在仅在几个保护区中被发现.

133
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:33,643
Their single horn can grow to over half a meter in length.
它们的单角长度可以超过半米.

134
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:45,800
Their prehensile lip makes their mouths
他们唇边张开的嘴唇

135
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,333
almost as nimble as a hand.
几乎像一只手一样敏捷.

136
00:10:48,490 --> 00:10:51,943
They can grasp tufts of grass and pick up fruit and leaves.
他们可以抓住一簇草,捡起水果和树叶.

137
00:10:55,710 --> 00:10:59,493
Rhinos eyesight is poor,but their sense of smell is sharp.
犀牛的视力较差,但嗅觉敏锐.

138
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:03,760
Scent glands on their feet leave a pungent trail
脚上的气味腺留下刺鼻的痕迹

139
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:05,240
wherever they walk back.
无论他们走到哪里.

140
00:11:07,610 --> 00:11:11,270
At midday,pre-monsoon heat nudges temperatures
在中午,季风前的热量推动温度升高

141
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:12,313
into the 40s.
进入40年代.

142
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:15,733
Rhinos seek refuge in the river.
犀牛在河里寻求庇护.

143
00:11:17,140 --> 00:11:19,980
As they are the most aquatic of all rhinos,
由于它们是所有犀牛中最水生的,

144
00:11:19,980 --> 00:11:22,183
